e bilateral relations, and promote election monitoring, as well as defend liberal democracy and the territorial integrity of Ukraine. Consulting media reports, official speeches, statements, published government documents, and archives of the Ukrainian Canadian Congress, Kordan highlights both continuities and shifts in policy during the leadership of four prime ministers, and reveals the undercurrents of contemporary Canadian foreign affairs. Investigating the progression of the Canada–Ukraine relationship, Strategic Friends queries the dynamics that have shaped Canada's foreign policy response in an age of change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCanada-Foreign relations-Ukraine. 0aCanada-Politics and government-1993-. 0aUkraine-Foreign relations-Canada. 0aUkraine-Politics and government-1991-. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Canadian.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311127268908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019z978311127498040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077355616440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773556164423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773556164/original  a978-3-11-127268-9  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-127498-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles